---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-top: 80px; padding-bottom: 32px;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: June 26, 2026 · How we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>AI Agents Hub is a static-only site</strong> (deployed on GitHub Pages). It runs no
          backend, offers no user accounts, and maintains no database of its own. By default, we
          <strong>do not actively collect your name, email, phone number, government ID, or any other
          personally identifiable information</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>The only technical logs that may be generated during your visit are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request time, requested URL, HTTP status, User-Agent, and Referer — generated by
            <strong>GitHub Pages / CDN edge nodes</strong> for security and operational purposes.</li>
          <li>Anti-bot and cache logs from <strong>Cloudflare</strong> (when enabled) for site
            acceleration and basic protection.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses <strong>no tracking cookies</strong> and integrates no third-party tracking
          scripts such as Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, or TikTok Pixel.
        </p>
        <p>
          The only thing written to your browser's <code>localStorage</code> is your
          <strong>theme preference</strong> (light / dark / system), used solely to restore your display
          choice on the next visit. This data <strong>stays on your device</strong> and is never uploaded
          to any server.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          This site contains many links to third-party websites (agent homepages, GitHub repos,
          sign-up pages, etc.). Once you click through and leave this site, <strong>we have no control
          over what those third parties collect</strong> or what cookies they set. Please review each
          third party's privacy policy before visiting.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Embedded resources</h2>
        <p>
          To improve the experience, some agent detail pages may embed videos or posts from
          <strong>YouTube, Bilibili, or X (Twitter)</strong>. These embeds are loaded by their
          respective platforms and may set cookies or collect IP addresses under their own privacy
          policies. If you do not wish to be tracked by these platforms, enable "Block third-party
          cookies" in your browser or use a privacy extension such as uBlock Origin.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Because this site maintains no personal data, we generally <strong>cannot offer</strong>
          services such as data access, correction, deletion, or export. If you spot something on this
          site that is inaccurate about you (for example, a misattributed tool), you can reach us via
          the <a href={`${base}/contact`}>contact page</a> and we will correct it as soon as we verify.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Minors</h2>
        <p>
          This site is aimed at developers and researchers with full civil capacity and is not designed
          for children under 14. If a minor visits the site through a guardian, the same policy
          applies.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Policy updates</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be revised as the product evolves (for example, if a subscription feature is
          added or a new platform is embedded). After a revision, the "Last updated" timestamp at the
          top of this page will be updated; no separate notice will be issued. Continued use of the
          site indicates acceptance of the current version.
        </p>

        <div class="verdict-box" style="margin-top: 32px;">
          <div class="label">TL;DR</div>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--text);">
            Static-only site · no tracking · no cookies · no personal data collected · the only
            thing in your local storage is your theme preference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
